287. Exp Mol Med. 2001 Jun 30;33(2):76-82. doi: 10.1038/emm.2001.14.

Cloning and characterization of 5'-upstream region of human phospholipase 
C-beta2 gene.

Yun ES(1), Lee SJ, Kim MJ, Ryu SH, Suh PG.

Author information:
(1)Dept. Life Science, Pohang University of Science and Technology, Korea.

5'-upstream region of the phospholipase C-beta2 gene, 810 bp, was cloned and 
characterized. S1 nuclease mapping and primer extension analyses revealed that a 
single transcriptional start site locates at 284 nucleotides upstream from the 
beginning of translation. The 5-upstream region lacks both TATA motif and 
typical initiator sequence, but retains GC-rich segment. Two putative regulatory 
regions, a negative region (-636/-588) and a positive region (-98/ -13) were 
identified in the upstream region of PLC-beta2 gene. We suggest that the 
transcription of PLC-beta2 may be regulated by binding of regulatory proteins to 
the negative and/or positive regulatory regions located in the upstream of the 
gene.

