has been evaluated as the best in the world. However, since the national economy 
in Japan has become recently suppressed it has become one of the big political 
problems to keep this system as same as before. In addition, the medical 
expenses for the elderly and aged people is now as high as 40% of all. In this 
meaning, we should create the better system by ourselves, based on ethical 
criteria, harmonized with the progress of medicine. In April of 2000, the new 
